## Acknowledgements

This project was developed as part of research on underactuated robotic systems
and optimal control theory. The theoretical foundations are based on the
following seminal works:

- Spong, M.W. (1995). "The Swing Up Control Problem for the Acrobot."
  IEEE Control Systems Magazine, 15(1), 49-55.
- Xin, X. & Kaneda, M. (2007). "Analysis of the Energy-Based Swing-Up
  Control of the Acrobot." International Journal of Robust and Nonlinear
  Control, 17(16), 1503-1524.
- Tedrake, R. "Underactuated Robotics: Algorithms for Walking, Running,
  Swimming, Flying, and Manipulation." MIT OpenCourseWare.

The mechanical parameters follow the Drake/Spong canonical benchmark, widely
adopted in the control systems community for reproducible research.

Special thanks to the open-source communities behind NumPy, SciPy, Numba,
and Matplotlib, whose tools made this simulation possible.
